{
  "id": "smallhold-6sk",
  "title": "Phase 0: Project Skeleton",
  "description": "Bootstrap the entire Cargo workspace, config system, database layer, core ID generation, logging infrastructure, and CLI skeleton. This is the foundation everything else builds on — if the skeleton is wrong, every later phase pays for it. The CLI-first approach is deliberate: if 'smallhold persona create writer' produces a sane DB row, the data model is right.",
  "design": "Single Cargo workspace. sqlx with compile-time query checking. sqlx-migrate for embedded migrations. clap v4 derive API. tracing + tracing-subscriber for structured logging. Custom snowflake generator (~50 lines with AtomicU64), no external dep.",
  "acceptance_criteria": "smallhold init creates config.toml and DB with correct schema; smallhold persona create writer inserts a row in accounts with a valid RSA keypair; all SQLite PRAGMAs active; snowflake IDs are time-sortable 64-bit integers",
